ks are grouped with each AD. Keep in mind AD\'s will also within the SV.',2,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L2','2018-08-27 23:16:16','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(969,76,'Engine / Modules Shop Inspection or Repair (Summary Pack/Minipack)','Shop visit reports, including dirty fingerprints, for all Engines,  module. At minimum the records should include the following: Release to Service Certificate, AD Status, SB Status, LLP Status., Engine Configuration Status, Incoming Inspection Report, Summary Report of Work Accomplished, Test Cell Report, After Test Cell Borescope Report(engines), and Fan Blade Plotting.',3,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L3','2018-08-27 23:16:57','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(970,76,'Test cell Run Report','Refer to Last Shop Visit\n',4,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L4','2018-08-27 23:17:28','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(971,76,'Engine Condition Monitoring (ECM) Report','\"A certified copy of the latest trend data for each engine, which must show no obvious deterioration in the on-wing performance of the engine. The trend data should be provided for the last 6 months\"\n',5,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L5','2018-08-27 23:18:04','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(972,76,'Borescope Reports','Latest borescope report and/or video (this is not the same as the borescope which is performed at redelivery)\n',6,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L6','2018-08-27 23:18:33','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(973,76,'Last On-Wing Ground Run','Latest engine ground run report (this is not the same as the ground run which is performed at redelivery)',7,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L7','2018-08-27 23:19:11','2018-11-07 21:58:25'),(974,76,'LLPs Back to Birth (full & Unbroken)','\"Certified records showing the accumulation of Hours and Cycles since new for each Life Limited Part of an engine. The record for each LLP (by LLP part number and serial number) shall show the serial number of the engine into which the LLP was installed when new, the Date, TSN & CSN of the engine at time of installation of the LLP and the Date, TSN & CSN of the engine at time of re