ished on each LLP. Note, this release to service certificate is critical for an LLP where a change of part number is implemented after the accomplishment of a service bulletin, airworthiness directive or manufacturer modification. The change of part number and reason for change shall be clearly identified.\nNon-incident/accident letters shall be provided for each engine into which each LLP has been installed.\nA copy of the most recent trend report provided by the Previous Operator for each engine.\nLog of Engine Flight Hours and Cycles, shop visits, modifications, ADs, Airframes to which fitted (manufacturerâ€™s serial numbers or registrations), installation data (date, TSN, CSN), removal data (date, TSN, CSN), Thrust Ratings.',8,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L8','2018-08-27 23:19:56','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2433,179,'Approved Release to Service Certification for Installed QEC Serialized Components','(If Available) and if required by Lease agreement \n',9,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L9','2018-08-27 23:20:56','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2434,179,'Approved Release to Service Certification for Installed Accessory Components','A304',10,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L10','2018-08-27 23:21:24','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2435,179,'Structures & Repairs - Dirty Finger Prints (DFPs)','\"Certified records showing accomplishment of repairs to the Engine since delivery from the manufacturer. Repairs not accomplished in accordance with the manufacturerâ€™s documentation must show evidence of approval of the repair data from the  State of Design of the aircraft and approval from the CAA of the State of Registration. A â€œNo Technical Objectionâ€ is not sufficient.\nMajor repairs must have an FAA Form 337 or EASA equivalent approving the actual accomplishment\"',11,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L11','2018-08-27 23:22:03','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2436,179,'Detailed Module information','(If Available) Refer to Shop Visit. \n',12,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','L12','2018-08-27 23:22:35','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2437,179,'SB Compl