'2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2592,194,'Landing Gear \"On-Wing Repair Documents','(If Available) \n',4,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X4','2018-08-29 01:43:49','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2593,194,'LLP Full and Unbroken Traceability Back to Birth','\"A certified list for each landing gear assembly showing all the LLPs incorporated in the assembly by P/N and S/N, showing the Cycles accumulated and Cycles remaining, including such other remaining life if operated at a different MTOW.\nCertified records showing the accumulation of Cycles since new for each Life Limited Part of a Landing Gear Assembly. the record for each LLP (by LLP part number and serial number) shall show the serial number (or Registration) of the airframe onto which the LLP was installed when new, the Date and CSN of the airframe at time of installation of the LLP and the date and CSN of the airframe at time of removal of the LLP. The record shall subsequently show the serial number (or Registration) of each airframe onto which the LLP has been installed, the Date and CSN of each such airframe at time of installation of the LLP and the Date and CSN of each such airframe at time of removal of the LLP. \nA Release to Service Certificate (FAA 8130-3, EASA Form 1 or equivalent) from new must be provided, or, if the LLP was installed new in a new airframe, a copy of the Manufacturerâ€™s log will suffice showing the part number and serial number of the LLP installed new at manufacture of the airframe.\nA Release to Service Certificate (FAA 8130-3, EASA Form 1 or equivalent) must also be provided for each maintenance activity (if applicable) accomplished on each LLP with a change of part number and reason for change noted. \nNon-incident/accident letters shall be provided for each airframe into which each LLP has been installed.\"',5,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X5','2018-08-29 01:44:27','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2594,194,'Approved Release to Service Certification and Applicable Shop Report for Installed Landing Gear','\"Release to Service Certificate from new or last maintenance activity for each serialized part of the assembly, and Release to Service Certificate for last overhaul for each serialized part of the assembly, and release to service record for installation on thec aircraft. Parts installed on the aircraft since the aircraft was new, and which have never been removed from the aircraft, may bec evidenced by delivery documentation provided at manufacture by the aircraft manufacturer.\"',6,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X6','2018-08-29 01:45:26','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2595,194,'Master AD Document','Listed in SV, otherwise all mixed in AD\'s Lists\n',7,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X7','2018-08-29 01:45:53','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2596,194,'ADs, Dirty Finger Print','\"The original dirty fingerprints, as recorded by an aircraft technician, of the most recent accomplishment of each task for each AD  requirement that would have fallen due since delivery from the manufacturer. The records should be organized to have the dirty fingerprints of each task grouped per AD so that all tasks are grouped with each AD.\"\n',8,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X8','2018-08-29 01:46:31','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2597,194,'Master SB Document','Listed in SV or data, otherwise all mixed in AD\'s Lists\n',9,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X9','2018-08-29 01:47:02','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2598,194,'SBs, Dirty Finger Print','Listed in SV or data plate otherwise all mixed in AD\'s Lists\n',10,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X10','2018-08-29 01:47:32','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2599,194,'Master Modification Documents (include STC / Part 21 Approval / Right to Use','As indicated \n',11,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X11','2018-08-29 01:48:08','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2600,194,'Mods, Dirty Finger Print Certification','\"Original records showing the accomplishment of each modification to the aircraft since delivery from the manufacturer. The  records should include the basis for certification (SB, STC, 8110-3, etc.)\"\n',12,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X12','2018-08-29 01:48:57','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2601,194,'Master SIL Documents','MBF / Airbus world.  From Operator for those are compliant with\n',13,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X13','2018-08-29 01:49:30','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2602,194,'Dirty Finger Print Records. Certified accomplishment of each SIL / SL','\"Original records showing the accomplishment of each SIL to the aircraft since delivery from the manufacturer. The records should include the basis for certification (SB, STC, 8110-3, etc.)\"\n',14,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X14','2018-08-29 01:50:04','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2603,194,'Landing Gear Removal / Installation Dirty Finger Print ','At Redelivery\n',15,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X15','2018-08-29 01:50:32','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2604,194,'Open Items / Deferred Items / HIL Items','\"Original records showing the accomplishment of each modification to the aircraft since delivery from the manufacturer. The records should include the basis for certification (SB, STC, 8110-3, etc.)\"\n',16,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X16','2018-08-29 01:51:09','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2605,194,'Landing Gear Reliability Report','At Redelivery\n',17,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X17','2018-08-29 01:51:35','2019-05-15 20:42:51'),(2606,194,'Photos - Landing Gear / Data Plates ','As indicated\n',18,1,1,1,1,'REPETITIVE','X18','2018-08-29 01:52:02','2019-05-15 20:42:51');
